<item>
            <title>[FLINK-5149] ContinuousEventTimeTrigger doesn&apos;t fire at the end of the window</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5149</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ContinuousEventTimeTrigger registers a timer when elements arrive. The timers might be registered past the end of the window. In this case, the window is cleaned up and doesn&apos;t fire at all. That is certainly not what users have in mind when they use the custom trigger.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I proposed to let it behave like a normal EventTimeTrigger in addition to its continuous firing capabilities. So it should fire at the end of the window regardless of timers set.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
